comment._content: His name was Charles Ernest Dixon according to Cambridge University Alumni www.ancestry.co.uk Entered: Coll. Oct. 21, 1890 Born: 22 Jan 1872 More Information: Matric. Non-Coll. Oct. 21, 1890. Of Norfolk. [Only] s. of John Gilbert (1859) [of St Andrew's-the-Less, Cambridge]. B. Jan. 22, 1872, at Norwich. School, Fowey Grammar, Cornwall. Migrated to CORPUS CHRISTI, Oct. 13, 1891; Scholar, 1892; Spencer Exhibitioner; B.A. 1893; M.A. 1897. Ord. deacon (York) 1895; priest, 1896; C. of St George's, Sheffield, 1895-8. C. of St James's-the-Less, Bethnal Green, 1898-1902. V. of St Jude's, Halifax, 1902-16. Chaplain to the Forces (T.A.), 1913-24. V. of St George's, Barnsley, 1916-28. V. of Pannal, 1928-40-. (Crockford, 1940.)
